  Project Title- Open Source Software Audit – Python
Introduction
Open Source Software (OSS) plays a crucial role in modern computing. It allows users to freely access, modify, and distribute software. This freedom promotes collaboration, transparency, and innovation.
Python is one of the most popular open-source programming languages in the world. It is widely used in various domains such as web development, artificial intelligence, data science, and automation.
This project focuses on analyzing Python as an open-source software. It includes both theoretical study and practical understanding through shell scripting in a Linux environment.
