 3. Part B – Linux Footprint
Python is widely used in Linux operating systems.
●	It is often pre-installed in Linux distributions
●	It can be installed using package managers
●	The executable is usually located in system directories
Python runs as a normal user, which enhances system security.
Linux provides a strong environment for Python development and execution. It allows users to manage packages, run scripts, and automate tasks efficiently.
________________________________________
 4. Part C – FOSS Ecosystem
Python is part of a large Free and Open Source Software (FOSS) ecosystem.
It supports various technologies:
●	Web frameworks (Django, Flask)
●	Data science tools (NumPy, Pandas)
●	Machine learning libraries (TensorFlow, Scikit-learn)
Python depends on lower-level languages like C for performance.
It has a huge global community that contributes to its development. Developers collaborate through platforms like GitHub and forums.
